Foreign worker visa From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia    Redirected from Foreign Worker Visa  Jump to navigation Jump to search This article does not cite any sources . Please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources . Unsourced material may be challenged and removed .  December 2009   Learn how and when to remove this template message  A foreign worker visa is an immigration document that allows a foreign national to temporarily live and work in a country. Ideally, such foreign nationals remedy a skill shortage in the host country, which gains support of business groups. See also  edit  Foreign worker visas of the United States  E-3 visa H-1B visa L-1 visa Retrieved from  httpsen.wikipedia.orgwindex.phptitleForeign_worker_visa oldid890323910  Categories  Visas Immigration law Employment of foreign-born Hidden categories Articles lacking sources from December 2009 All articles lacking sources